\subsection{Wild Artin slopes of a local field}
\begin{definition}\label{lf.wild_slopes}
\uses{lf.galois_invariants,nf.galois_group,nf.is_galois}
Let $K$ be a finite {{KNOWL('nf.is_galois', 'Galois')}} extension of $\Q_p$ for some prime $p$.  The **wild Artin slopes** indicate the locations and sizes of jumps in the filtration of the {{KNOWL('nf.galois_group', 'Galois group')}} by higher ramification groups.  See {{KNOWL('lf.galois_invariants', 'Galois invariants')}} of a local number field for more information.
\end{definition}


